First angling Center in northwest China Opens
Over 10,000 angling lovers gathered in the suburb of Xi'an, capital
city of Shaanxi Province, earlier this week to mark the inauguration of
the first angling center in northwest China.
The angling center, occupying 33,000 square meters in Chang'an County,
contains three fishing ponds and a lake with a combined water-locked
area of 20,000 square meters.
The center has poured at least 200,000 fish of various species into the
water. The largest weighs 12 kg.
Other material comforts include a hot spring bathroom, a dance hall and
restaurants.
